If God is all I need, then why do I continuely search for other things in empty spaces. It makes no sence. On the surface I don't feel myself, or like the person I really want to be...someone completely devoted to God. Deep down I really want to make the right choices, and give everything to God, but I don't seem capable of geting past some stupid things. Growing up in the church is bitter-sweet. On one hand, I've grown up knowing God, and realizing what life is really about. But on the other hand, now a days, I really dont know why I believe what I do anymore. Beliving in him just because I have all my life isn't good anymore. This probably sounds really weird, but its like theres two of me. The one part is struggling with worldly things,while the other is screamin God is everythin you need, just trust him. I know with out a doubt, 100% there is a God, but what exactly I'm supposed to do with my life . I want to give up and just say screw it all, but some part of me won't let go. About 4 years ago, I felt a call to something. I can't explain it, but I know God wants me to do something big for him. But if I don't get by these struggles, I'll never do it. If I don't throw away all my dreams and self-ambitions I'll never reach it. It's all my fault this stuff is happening too. I never read my Bible, I never pray meaninful prayers or heart-filled ones, I always re-commit my life to God, but it always ends in failure. I seem so determined, but always screw up...and get so ticked off. Everytime I screw up, its like crucifying him all over again...and knowing that makes me feel even worse. But it's because of his amazing grace that I can get back up, and try again. It's because of him I'm here, and it's because of him I'll never give up. Thinking of all my friends or people  who don't believe in God; if I put my self in their shoes, goin through life not knowin why I'm here, and the ultimate happiness and fulfilment, ad a personal realtionship with JC, thats gotta be 100x worse than what I'm goin through. No matter what I go through, he's there. And from now on I'm always gonna seek him first.











If you think I'm stupid or lame for sayin all this or believing this, I stopped caring awhile ago, :P

Images on the sidewalk speak of a dream's descent 
Washed away by storms to graves of cynical lament 
Dirty canvases to call my own 
Protest limericks carved by the old pay phone 

In your picture book I'm trying hard to see 
Turning endless pages of this tragedy 
Sculpting every move you compose a symphony 
You plead to everyone, "see the art in me" 

Broken stained-glass windows, the fragments ramble on 
Tales of broken souls, an eternity's been won 
As critics scorn the thoughts and works of mortal man 
My eyes are drawn to you in awe once again 

And in your picture book I'm trying hard to see 
Turning endless pages of this tragedy 
Sculpting every move you compose a symphony 
You plead to everyone, "see the art in me"
Words cant describe how awesome you are God
